acl: set: Usage: infinit-acl acl set [OPTIONS]
Set ACLs

Options:
  -h, --help                show this help message
      --compatibility-version arg  compatibility version to force
  -s, --script              suppress extraneous human friendly messages and use JSON output
  -a, --as arg              user to run commands as (default: akim)
      --path arg            file whose acl to set
  -u, --user arg            user to set acl for
  -g, --group arg           group to set acl for
  -m, --mode arg            access mode to set: r, w, rw, none (default: null)
  -o, --others-mode arg     access mode to set for other users: r, w, rw, none (default: null)
  -i, --enable-inherit      make new files and directories inherit permissions
      --disable-inherit     make new files and directories not inherit permissions
  -R, --recursive           set acl recursively
  -t, --traverse            set read permission on parent directories
  -v, --verbose             use verbose output
  -f, --fetch               fetch acl from https://beyond.infinit.sh
      --fallback-xattrs     use fallback special file if extended attributes are not supported

